een Bieber and Fred wouldn&#39;t be all too surprising. The pair have worked together in the past, most notably on Bieber&#39;s <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/listen-justin-bieber-ed-sheerans-new-song-dont-care-2486213">&#39;I Don&#39;t Care&#39; with Ed Sheeran</a> , which Fred Again.. co-wrote and co-produced.</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/justin-bieber-justice-review-2900928"><b>Justin Bieber – &#39;Justice&#39; review: pop star finds his purpose again</b></a></strong></li></ul><p> Bieber has seemingly been working on new music since at least October, and has shared new images and clips of himself in the studio since then. Back in September, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/justin-bieber-is-working-on-new-music-with-mk-gee-3790800">Mk.gee revealed that he had been working with the singer on new material</a> as Bieber “searched” for his next phase.</p><p> “He&#39;s searching. Anything that comes out of his mouth: That&#39;s pop music. You can really do pretty wild stuff behind that, just because it represents something,” Mk.gee said at the time.</p><p> Justin Bieber&#39;s last album came in the form of 2021&#39;s &#39;Justice&#39;. In a <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/justin-bieber-justice-review-2900928">four star review</a> , Will Lavin wrote for <em>NME</em> : “With bangers, ballads and heartfelt moments, the hopeless romantic with a penchant for self reflection and tackling world issues is back. Beliebers rejoice!” </p><figure id="attachment_3846149" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3846149" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3846149" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/justin-bieber@2000x1270.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/justin-bieber@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025